commit.message: don't commit Makefile.in
Release 1.2

take attribute arguments into account

Coccinelle complains about unused metavariables.  Adjust the analysis to take
into account metavariables used in attribute arguments.

Motivated by a semantic patch found in

https://github.com/coccinelle/coccinelle/issues/363#issuecomment-2016836755
can only optimize S body if no attached used after position variables
include module name
better support of ellipses in macro parameter lists
tests for issues around end attributes and typedef inference in SmPL and C
detect type when decl followed by attribute
use lexer type_names to propagate type names from - to + code
reduce some line lengths
allow ...... as a #define param in SmPL
consider the possibility of inheritance; not supported in SmPL
more informative error message for struct handling
support namespace with no name in a forgotten case
more debug information
ensure that retrieved file names actually are source code files
don't make a template a qualtype if there has not been a ::; testcase doesn't parse, but gets past qualtype detection
not handling :: intline, used for namespaces
like size_t, ssize_t isn't a keyword in C++
cope with ::new; the test doesn't parse, but at least it gets out of parsing_hacks
more informative error
correct treatment of asm to keep asm token and put argument tokens in the right order
avoid asm, which may contain :: for other reasons
recognize star
ptrdiff_t should not be a keyword in C++
don't print message for every example
qualified expression may end with an operator
need to skip spaces after the :: after a template
visitor needs to recursively process the name to the right of a ::
improve spacing
